CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 5, 1955, pg. 1B reads: "Prime Minister tells newspaper, men at dinner in Press Club of his experiences in Pittsburgh twenty-eight years ago and of his plans for making Nigeria an independent, self-sufficient nation."
TitMainTitle: Eastern Nigerian Prime Minister Nnamdi Azikiwe wearing light colored agbada, and dark cap, standing at head of banquet table speaking to group of men, including Bill Nunn Sr. seated on right, in Press Club
